byline.original: Correspondence of The New-York Daily Times

lead_paragraph: There is scarcely anything of interest to write from this point by the present mail. Business has been remarkably dull for three or four weeks past, mostly attributable to the fact that many nervous persons are afraid that "Nicaragua is going to break up the Panama route."
